==Inconsistency in rating== This article was assessed as B Class for WP Military History, but marked as needing an infobox for WP Aviation (B5=no). Infobox added and assessment made for WP Aviation. However, B1=No. A majority of citations lack page numbers and several of them appear to be to multiple volumes of a work , {{cite book|last=Gorrell|first= Col. Edgar S.|title=History of the American Expeditionary Forces Air Service, 1917-1919|series = Series |volume= Vol. |year= |publisher=National Archives and Records Service, General Services Administration|location= Washington, DC|oclc=215070705|pages = }}. It is also assessed as a list for WP Aviation and WP United States, but as an article for WP Military History --[[User:Lineagegeek|Lineagegeek]] ([[User talk:Lineagegeek|talk]]) 20:49, 24 February 2015 (UTC)
==Move== The American Forces engaged in France during World War I were the [[American Expeditionary Forces]]. This article should be moved to reflect the "s" at the end of its name. --[[User:Lineagegeek|Lineagegeek]] ([[User talk:Lineagegeek|talk]]) 20:49, 24 February 2015 (UTC)
